      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "@michaelfolkson You can run multiple `bitcoind` processes on the same machine, whether they operate on the same chain or different chains. But at least for now there is no way to have one process run on multiple chains simultaneously, and I don't expect there will be, so it's unclear what specifying multiple chains would mean.\r\n\r\nIt's also unrelated to this PR.",
