      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "It would IMO be unnecessary complication to run multiple chains in one process. When you can solve something using multiple processes that tends to be (definitely from a decoupling angle) a better design.\r\n\r\nOfftopic also: I understand the confusion though. In retrospect I think we should have bitten the bullet and switched to `-chain=X`, instead of an option per chain, such an option maps much better to how things are handled under the hood. But I think that ship sailed.",
